                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ok ive been meaning to write up a little faq about this for a while now so here goes.
<br />

<br />
As you may or may not know guilds in eq2 have levels. They gain exp through a series of quests given by NPCs in which ever city you are affiliated with. 
<br />

<br />
Within each city there are 5 different factions. In Freeport for instance there is Militia faction, Coalition of Tradesfolk faction, Academy of Caster faction, etc. There is one NPC for each faction that gives writ quests. In the Freeport Militia for example, Trooper Bonesaw is the writ giver. In the quest journal writ quests are listed under City Tasks. Completing the writ quests for these factions accomplishes 3 things.
<br />

<br />
1) The guild receives exp (if you are a patron)
<br />
2) You receive status points (explained later)
<br />
3) You increase your personal faction with whomever you did the writ for
<br />

<br />
One important thing to note is that ONLY Patrons of a guild can actually level the guild up in this way. Non patrons still receive status points and faction. Non patrons can not use the status merchants around the city. Non patrons can ONLY use the faction merchants which are located in the Faction headquarters themselves. The faction merchants are currently broken (to the best of my knowledge) however in theory. Status merchants are called City Merchants. Faction merchants are just called "merchants" but they are located in the Faction hqs.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Now what the status merchants sell is dependant upon your guild level. At guild level 10 for instance, you can buy a horse for 5gold and 50k status points, which as you know is MUCH cheaper than buying a horse retail. You can check your status points in the Persona window (hit P).
<br />

<br />
When faction merchants are fixed, what they sell is totally dependant on your personal faction with which ever group you are with. So if you are a non patron, and thus not allowed to shop at the status merchants, it would behoove you to stick with one faction only. That way you can unlock the cool stuff to spend your status points on. Patrons can use BOTH faction merchants and city merchants, but even so its probably better for you to stick to one faction to unlock the faction merchant when they actually fix the faction merchants that is.
<br />

<br />
You can get 2 writ quests at a time from each writ giver for a total of 10 writ quests at once. Some of you may be thinking that you can only get one writ from each faction at a time, but iff you open a dialog with the writ giver, then BEFORE you accept the quest, open a second dialog, you can get BOTH quests. This makes leveling up the guild and getting status points much faster.
<br />

<br />
Anyways this post will be a work in progress. Post question on whatever I left out and I will update it with new info along the way. Enjoy.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
