                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">You can do writs for all the Heralds.  A developer explained on the EQ2 forums that, with the way the faction adjustments were set for completing writs, doing writs for all four (soon to be five) heralds would result in a small positive adjustment for all the factions.  Doing a writ from only one herald will result in large positive adjustments for their particular faction and small negative adjustments in all the other factions.  However, you will never lower your faction so far that you cannot perform writs for these factions.
<br />

<br />
Because the Herald for artisan writs is not in game yet, it is currently not possible to raise your faction with the tradeskill faction of your home city.  They have promised to address this once they introduce the artisan heralds, presumably by resetting everyone's tradeskill faction to indifferent.
<br />

<br />
I am paraphrasing what the developer said.  I will try to see if I can find the post on the EQ2 boards and link them here.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Juneau, Human Fury of Freeport (EQ2)</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
